Class TransformIteration<I,O,E extends Exception>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.complexible.common.iterations.TransformIteration<I,O,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - the input type
    O - the iteration type
    E - the exception thrown
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, Iteration<O,E>

    public final class TransformIteration<I,O,E extends Exception>
extends Object
implements Iteration<O,E>
    Implementation of an Iteration which will apply a function to transform the results of an inner iterator to a different type.

    2.0

        public void close()

        Close the iterator. This signals that it is ok to free up any resources used by the implementation. It is expected, but not required, that subsequent calls to Iteration.hasNext() or Iteration.next() would fail and throw an exception, such as an IllegalStateException.
